==English==
===Etymology===
{{G.}} ''[[Wiener Würstchen]]'' "[[Viennese]] sausage", because they were originally made in [[Vienna]], Austria. However, in Vienna they are called "[[Frankfurter]]".

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːnə(r)|-iːnə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{US}} a [[sausage]] made from [[beef]], [[chicken]] or [[pork]], used in [[hot dog]]s; a [[frankfurter]] (''British'')
#{{US}},(colloquial) [[penis]]
#{{US}} someone who is nervous or afraid to partake in certain activities

